Jane Elizabeth Keller, a daughter of Dr. and Mrs. Donal E. Keller of Manhasset, L.I., was married yesterday to Lawrence Alan Gordon, a son of Mr. and Mrs. Haskell R. Gordon of Worchester, Mass. Rabbi Stanley Davids performed the ceremony at the summer home of the bride's parents in Westhampton Beach, L.I.

The bride, 35 years old, was until recently the vice president of marketing at the Solgar Vitamin Company in Lynbrook, L.I. A graduate of Smith College, she received a master's degree in public health from the University of Michigan and an M.B.A. from New York University. Her father is the chief of dentistry at St. Francis Hospital in Roslyn, L.I. Her mother, Barbara Keller, is the director of the Herricks Community Center in New Hyde Park, L.I.

The bridegroom, 36, is the chief operating officer and the executive vice president of the Fair Discount Department Stores in Worcester. He graduated cum laude from Tufts University and received a master's degree in management from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology. His father, who is retired, was co-owner of Fair Discount.